snippet.textDisplay:
In summer 2020, Pogba will be on the books at 45 million. Even if he is sold for 100 million, United will have gained only 55 million. Who can the club buy for 55 million?
The Glazers have determined that it's cheaper to renew the contracts for Jones, Rojo, Lingard, Bailly, Dalot, F-Mensah and Pereira than to sell them. They are right. Selling these seven players will generate about 100 million and replacing them will cost 300 million. The Glazers don't have 200 million sitting around and therefore, they are not buying players.
In addition, unlike every other top club, they don't have the money to rebuild the urine-reeking and rat-infested sh!thole named, Old Toilet.
Like a vaseline covered turd, the club is continuing to slide into irrelevance.
